<subSubSection id="C355650F7475655FFF21F99AA0FD318C" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="745" pageId="3" pageNumber="744" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF036847475655FFF21F99AA0023124" blockId="3.[178,1085,1553,1605]" lastBlockId="4.[178,1085,219,358]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="745" pageId="3" pageNumber="744">
D i a g n o s i s Female: Malar sulcuswith triangular fovea below eye, narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F4D0774756558FF42F9A7A36D3606" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[209,354,1583,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Sigmophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="744" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis id="B93BEA9674756558FF42F9A7A36D3606" box="[209,354,1583,1604]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="744">S. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, less than one-third the height of the malar space; transverse carina behind lateral ocelli, second transvers carina behind lateral ocelli, second transverse carina posterior to median ocellus; scape 5.6 times as long as broad; male antenna with whorled setae of F1 reaching to two-thirds the length of F3; metanotum rounded and about 4 times as broad as long; length of last gastral tergite 1.7 times as long as its basal breadth (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE4B757472655FFE9FFED8A00D3124" author="YEFREMOVA Z" box="[268,514,336,358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="745" pagination="197 - 199" refId="ref4314" refString="YEFREMOVA Z. A. &amp; E. N. YEGORENKOVA (2009): A review of the subfamily Tetrastichinae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae) in Yemen, with descriptions of new species. - Fauna of Arabia 24: 197 - 199." type="journal article" year="2009">YEFREMOVA et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF036847472655FFF21FEFEA60331EB" blockId="4.[178,1085,373,425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="745">
